1.Take any csv/text file of 2+ GB of your choice. 

2.Read the file.( Present approach of reading the file)

3.Try different methods of file reading eg: Dask, Modin, Ray, pandas and present your findings in terms of computational efficiency.

4.Perform basic validation on data columns, for example,remove special character , white spaces from the column name, etc.

5.Create a YAML file and write the column name in YAML file. Define separator of read and write file, column name in YAML.

6.Validate number of columns and column name of ingested file with YAML.

7.Write the file in pipe separated text file (|) in gz format.

8.Create a summary of the file.

9.Print the total number of rows.

10.Print total number of columns.

11.Print file size.
